step.reason:
%text
If the required normal be $AP$, then 
%
\begin{align}
\frac{y_P - 2}{x_P-1} &= m_N\text{ (normal's slope)} \\
\text{But }m_N\cdot m_T &= -1 \text{ where }m_T = \left[\frac{dy}{dx}\right]_{x=x_P} \\
\therefore m_N &= -\frac{1}{\underbrace{\left(\dfrac{x_P}{2}\right)}_{\frac{dy}{dx}}} = -\frac{2}{x_P} \\
\implies \frac{y_P - 2}{x_P-1} &= -\frac{2}{x_P}
\end{align}
